"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-at-paris-olympics-women-athletes-finally-reach-parity\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Athletes competing in the women's steeplechase during the US Olympic Team Trials at Hayward Field.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6469689546120867e-14, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  PublishedJun 26, 2024, 05:45 PM  UpdatedJun 26, 2024, 09:06 PM  PARIS-Once seen as a \\\"celebration of manly virtue\\\" without women athletes, the modern Olympics will reach gender parity for the first time during the 2024 Paris Games, 128 years since its first edition.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the ancient Greek event was revived by French aristocrat Pierre de Coubertin in the late 19th century, he saw it as a celebration of gentlemanly athleticism \\\"with female applause as its reward\\\".\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.7630048487750031, \"rank\": 0.30722036633224775, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7981136314154976, \"rank\": 0.25024897043236893, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 685, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1924, the last time the Olympics were held in Paris, just 4 per cent of competitors were female and they were restricted to sports considered suitable for them, such as swimming, tennis and croquet.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983474481, \"rank\": 1.6526737159403178e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Things have come a long way since.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For the first time in Olympic history we are going to have gender parity on the field,\\\" Marie Sallois, the International Olympic Committee's (IOC) director in charge of gender equality, said of the July 26-Aug 11 event.\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.56231752647767e-30, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It took a very long time for us to finally get to 44 per cent (of women) in London in 2012, the first edition at which women could take part in all the sports, then 48 per cent in Tokyo (in 2021).\\\"\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999988634833336, \"rank\": 1.1272663177340096e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999959053213546, \"rank\": 4.094441195715991e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The barriers for women were once so high they were forced to compete in a rival \\\"Women's Olympics\\\" in the 1920s.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1928 in Amsterdam, they were allowed to compete in athletics for the first time, but the sight of exhausted female runners after the 800m final appalled male onlookers so much that they were excluded again.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 0.999999996227416, \"rank\": 3.770159776283607e-09, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until 1960, women were barred from competing in any race of more than 200m, and even in 1976, women's events made up only a quarter of the Olympic programme.\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And long considered unable to cope with the physical demands of the marathon, they were finally allowed to take part for the first time at the Los Angeles Games in 1984.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Games will not only feature as many women as men, it will also give greater prominence to women's events.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of the men's marathon being the athletics event leading up to the closing ceremony, it will be the women's.\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have made a lot of effort to organise the women's events to ensure they get visibility, meaning over the weekend when there are more viewers, or during prime time,\\\" Sallois added.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the opening ceremony, the IOC has also suggested each national delegation nominate two flag carriers, a man and a woman.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.56231752647767e-30, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Sallois conceded elite sport still had lots of work to do to achieve genuine gender parity.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among coaching staff at the last Olympics in Tokyo, just 13 per cent of coaches were women.\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2825, \"end\": 2830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999959053213546, \"rank\": 4.094441195715991e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports administration remains overwhelmingly male, including in national Olympic delegations and in the federations that run sports.\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC itself has never had a female leader and its membership - made up of 105 delegates who vote on key decisions - remains almost 60 per cent male.AFP  Olympics 2024  Olympics  Gender issues  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.56231752647767e-30, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": []}]}"